-- Axis Ex-Chairman to Receive $36 Million Payoff, Times Reports
-- B y   J o h n   G l o v e r
-- 2012-07-22T06:34:31Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-07-22/axis-ex-chairman-to-receive-36-million-payoff-times-reports.html
John Charman, ousted as chairman of
reinsurer  Axis Capital Holdings Ltd. (AXS)  last month, will receive a
$36 million payoff, the  Sunday Times  reported, citing filings
with the Securities & Exchange Commission.  Charman will get $13.9 million in place of pension payments
as well as shares worth $22 million, the newspaper said. He also
owns a $78.8 million stake in Axis, which he set up in 2001,
according to Sunday Times.  To contact the reporter on this story:
John Glover in London at 
